caption: This is a very small sandwich joint that packs a ton of flavors. My coworkers and I found it while attending conference near by the convention center. I had the korean bbq sandwich. It was delicious. sweet and tangy, with a spicy kick. paired with some juice asian slaw. One of the best fusion sandwich i've had in DC.
Pretty darn good with surprising flavors. Would eat again, and the bread was defiantly out of this world for good texture.
Delicious sandwiches + quick, efficient, and flexible customer service. Very consistent, high quality.

Sun de vich is one of my favorite places near the are, I have been getting Lima but this time I tried the madrid with eggs, it was delicious this place it’s worth the price and I’m happy with the service they give to you everyone is so sweet and nice!.
Among the very best jerk chicken sandwiches in the world. Big up !

I found a hidden gem of a sandwich shop today in DC. The name is “Sundevich”. After reading the menu it was very difficult to decide what to have as all the sandwiches sounded so delicious. I decided on “the Mexican city”. There are no words to describe this place. It was like poetry between two pieces of bread. The staff was so friendly and made me feel like family and the food came out quickly. I’m giving them five stars only because I can’t give them 10. I will definitely go back and recommend this place to both family and friends ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

There’s a  million places to get a sandwich in DC,  but the only one you need to know about is Sundevich. First of all I could eat here every day and never get tired of it, so much to choose from. The bread is so fresh and the meats are  seasoned to perfection. You can tell that the people who prepare the food really care. The staff goes above and beyond to make sure you leave here happy and well feed. I hope they open in Maryland soon because I drive from Laurel Maryland all the way to NW DC just for their food. THIS PLACE IS AWESOME!!!
Great spot to grab a sandwich to go. Experience is hit or miss depending on which sandwiches you get. Lima, Seoul, Paris are on point.
Sundevich has some of the best sandwiches anywhere in DC! Named after different cities every one is delicious. And even the ones that sound like an odd combination are amazing!

The Seoul is my personal fav but you can’t go wrong with any of the sandwiches!! Everything I’ve tried is great. I’ve also seen customers order the sandwich as a salad, not sure if that’s a menu hack but worth a try if you’re gluten free!

Their online order system directs people to the Georgetown location with such frequency that they have a sign by the register and disclaimers up top on their front page. None of this is visible when you click “order” on the google page, only after you’ve already paid. Ended up paying double for one sandwich. This is just irresponsible.

I love their sandwiches, they have fresh ingredients and taste delicious. Great bread, crusty and warm. The meat inside of the bread was really good. It is worth of your money. It makes my craving satisfied. Staff wear masks for safety precautions, during this pandemic Covid19. Quick service, helpful and friendly staff. Absolutely Recommended!
Fantastically delicious! I'm working my way through their menu in order. So far, my favorites are the Havana and Memphis. Cairo is a unique veggie option.
Everything very delicious they prepare it for you at the moment.
(Translated by Google) All very tasty  (Original) Todo muy rico
I’ve tried a little over half of the sandwiches here, 80% of them are outstanding to me, some are not for me personally, but The Memphis, Kingston, Athens, Seoul, and Lima are unreal!
It was an amazing experience to have tasted Persian sandwiches again after a long time!
Yummy,its the most delicious food ive ever tried.try it once and u become addicted
Good variety, quick service, delicious!
Such a unique and expansive menu, nice staff,  and overall cute place!
Flavorful sandwiches, great quality!
Great sandwiches. Had the Madrid and was quite delicious!
Wonderful hot subs.
Not the best experience tonight.  The bread was hard and dry.  The sandwich a bit cold and way less meat and filling than usual.  Hopefully this was anomaly...

Great local sandwich shop! There are so many options from around the world, so there should be something for everyone that you go with. The space is trendy and industrial, but is a little small. Nonetheless, there is a decent amount of seating, and they get the sandwiches out to you quickly. Highly recommended if you are looking for a quick bite in the area.

I can't say enough good things about this place. I got the Beirut sandwich which had brined vegetable. My only desire would be some some jalapeno to add a little kick. My wife ordered the Seoul and substituted with spicy slaw; it was one of the best beef sandwiches I ever had. Almost like bohn mi.
Best sandwich shop around the convention center for sure.
Always try and go here when I'm in the area. To notch (non standard) sandwiches, the Athens is my go to order (grilled lamb).
Excellent taste.
Its worth it
Small space, but the choice of sandwiches on quality baguettes is excellent. Fresh ingredients and friendly service.
Pricy, but really really good.
I can't say enough about this place! I went three days in a row and tried different sandwiches each time. All of them were great,  my favorite was the Beirut,  but there is one for every taste.

Sandwich themes from all over the world. Each sandwich is named for a city and the ingredients themed for that part of the globe. Seem to be fresh ingredients and taste delicious. A relatively recent addition of egg-based sandwiches (instead of the mostly other meat options or a few veggie only) was a welcome improvement too. Grab and go or eat-in in a casual environment.

(Translated by Google) Seoul Sandwich is delicious! It was expensive because it was $ 13, but it was long and large. It's really bulgogi and I thought of Subway but it's a much better sandwich! I've solved lunch all day here.  (Original) 서울샌드위치 맛있어요! 13불이라서 비싼가했는데, 길고 양이 많더라고요. 진짜 불고기 들어있었고 서브웨이 생각했지만 그거보다 훨씬 맛있는 샌드위치에요! 일정 내내 점심은 여기서 해결했습니다~ 사람이 많이 몰려서 점심시간 조금 전에 가세요!~

I usually stop here every time I am in DC.  The price may look high but they give you a sandwich that is two meals so the price is actually spot on. The food is flavorful and the staff are always nice. Seating is very limited so I always take my food to go.
good food
The avocado and chicken sandwich was fantastic!
Sundevich sandwiches are amaaaaazing. Literally never had one less than superb. Friendly staff, fast service, reasonable prices. Truly drool-worthy.

The food and wait time were great. It may seem a tad pricey but the portion sizes are generous and the ingredients fresh.  The cashier was rude. I'm not expecting Starbucks-level perk, but if I say, "hello" or "thank you" I prefer not to get a stone-faced silence, but looking at other reviews, this seems to be the exception and not the rule.
Favorite sandwich in DC

Great service and tasty sandwiches. Be prepared to get huge portion (whole baguette stuffed with rich fillings)! Good value for money as depending on the kind you choose, you pay appr. 13 $ for a big meal. I would recommend it for vegetarians too, though not sure they have gluten-free option.
Place for creative and delicious sandwiches. The day soup was great as well. The location is kind of odd but totally worth it!
My boss told me to visit this place during a business trip. He swore by it. Such good sandwiches! Oh my goodness, an absolute must try if you are in D.C.! Yummm! 😊

Accidentally stumbled on this place back in 2014 and been stumbling back ever since. Not exactly a low cost sandwich at first glance, but quality ingredients and memorable dishes keep me coming back to this small local business.

Ever go out to lunch with friends, and one person wants Italian, another wants Chinese, and you were in the mood for Mediterranean. Check out SUNdeVICH. It's a great little spot for sandwiches that truly has something for everyone's tastebuds. Sandwiches are named after cities around the world, and feature a fun assortment of toppings. I'm partial to the Seoul — with the beef bulgogi, kimchi, and asian slaw — but the Kingston, Rome, and Havana are also great. Sandwiches are also a decent size, so you can eat half for lunch and have a bonus sandwich later. Great selection of rootbeers, too.  Note: The address is on 9th St, but it's actually about 20 yards off of 9th down an alley.
Love this place, great sandwiches. Best in the area, especially for lunch!  Seoul is my favorite but all the ones I've tried have been tasty. Buenos Aires is my second favorite.
Damn good sandwich, with good flavors.....very fresh🤗
Small place that was busy but not crazy at lunchtime. 20+ sandwiches representing different cities. Bread was great, crusty and warm. Meat was really nice as time we extremely flavorful.
Great flavors and cute setting
Simple, creative combinations that go beyond the ingredients to really hit the spot. They have breakfast sandwiches as well and the eggs are amazing.
Great big sandwitch , affordable prices.
The bread was pretty tough and dry but it was still enjoyable. The tzatziki was amazing. Keep in mind seating inside is very limited.
Excellent food and a very nice, if small, seating area.

Went here and got the Rome sandwich. Amazingly fresh sub roll, spring mix, and deli meat. The sandwich was very flavorful and had just the right amount of every ingredient so you could taste each ingredient in every bite. It's a small place inside so don't expect to find much seating. Most people seemed to get their meals to go. The service was very fast. I'm not from here but want to go back for more before I leave.

You know it's a good sign when they hollow out their rolls so that more stuffing can fit inside these amazing sandwiches. Diverse menu with lots of creative pairings from around the world. Went with a few friends and we each got different sandwiches and shared them all. I liked them all!  The space leaves something to be desired, however, as there's a weird line that forms toward the door as people decide what they want. I didn't even realize there were sides until I turned the corner otherwise I would have ordered some.  But that didn't get in the way of another amazing sandwich from Sundevich.
It's expensive (most sandwiches are $15-$20) but my goodness they're tasty.  Efficient lunch-counter style service.
Great sandwich. One of the best I've had. Quality ingredients make the difference
Excellent subs, got the jerk chicken one. Quick service and turnaround, highly recommended.

(Translated by Google) It's a sandwich shop just off the street. Tourists feel a little jealous of the entrance, The inside is simple and the atmosphere is good.  The sandwich menu was named after the city and the contents were easy to imagine.  The taste was very good.  Because the amount is about double that Japanese thinks, those who eat less may be half full.  Sandwiches are priced at around 10 dollars, but are reasonable considering the amount and taste.  (Original) 少し路地に入ったところにあるサンドイッチ屋です。 観光客は少し躊躇する入り口の雰囲気ですが、 中はシンプルだし雰囲気も良いです。  サンドイッチはメニューが都市の名前になっていて内容もイメージしやすかったです。  味はすごく良かったです。  量が日本人の考える倍くらいあるので少食の人は半分でお腹いっぱいになるかもしれません。  サンドイッチは大体10ドル〜、という価格設定ですが、量と味を考えれば妥当です。
That's a great sandwich!
Love their sandwich menu. Try Lima, Capri and Kingston--these are my favorites!
Awesome creative sandwiches and a bargain for the money!
Their sandwiches are always delicious and fresh. Try the "Istanbul" and the "Beirut"--my favorites.

Cute place! A little more expensive than I would like, but high quality, fresh ingredients. Interesting (and tasty) sandwich combos - an entire world city theme. Wish they had a couple more vegetarian options or substitutes though.
Oh my g a w D. Go to this sandwich place and thank me later. I'd always order two cuz I could never decide which to get. Personal favorites were Buenos Aires and the Tehran
Delicious sandwiches and friendly staff. Great selection and very affordable too!
This is a great find. Food id's fresh and very tasty
Their sandwiches are great. Ingredients are fresh. You definitely get your money's worth.
Great food! Fresh ingredients and unique menu options. Love this place. Staff is very friendly and helpful.
The sandwiches are great but 20 bucks for a drink a sando and a side seems pretty steep.

What can I say? The sandwiches seem pricey but in this case you get what you pay for. I was in town for a conference and stopped in for a quick lunch. Loved the Tehran, it made two meals for me. Everything tasted fresh and good. Will definitely go back the next time I'm in D.C.!

A hidden gem. Was recommended on a blog about DC and I’m so happy we ate here. Visited for lunch on a weekday and shop was busy but service fast. A huge variety of sandwiches to choose from, named the the city the fillings originate. I had the Capri - fresh mozzarella, sliced tomato and basil pesto, simply delicious! Particularly liked that it wasn’t all bread, but the bread was delicious, chewy and fresh. There were stools and benches to sit at and enjoy your food, or many do takeaway.
Fantastic and creative sandwiches. Only minor complaint was I asked for a simple grilled cheese for the kids (bread and cheese) and they charged me the full price of a sandwich.
Really fresh simple and tasty
Probably the best sandwich i have ever had 😃 (Memphis sandwich)
Awesome sandwich. Fresh and quality ingredients.

I was from out of town , here for a business trip ,and looking for something to eat . The place was super hidden and warm when I got inside . The size of the sub  was a good for the money but probably not something I would go back to . But it's like a little gem .
Good sandwiches but no AC, rxpensive, and long wait even when small line. Would recomend the Seoul tho!

This is a gem hinden in an alley, if you can find t It yiu?'re in kufj! The sandwich are amazing, and well worth the wait even if there's a line! They are great for a quick grab and go meal, and the portions are big! If you aren't starving you may even be able to share. The Jamaican Jerk chicken is a great combo of flavors--highky recommend!

This location is rather small but we just went in to grab and go, it was perfect for that. The staff was excellent and these sandwhiches were phenominal. I had the kingston the chicken was very juicy which was great but there wasn't much jerk flavor in it. It was a good sandwhich still. Way better than all the other subsandwhich competitiors..
The sandwiches were fresh and high quality ingredients a burst of flavor in every bite!
Great sandwiches. Hurt the wallet though
Super great sandwich.
Phenomenal
Really neat place, I just wish they would toast the bread! There were a couple of vegetarian options but my weakness for pesto blinded me from the other options.

I knew I would love this place before even getting through the door. It's tiny, cute, and clean, and has a corner devoted to cactus terrariums 🌵 The menu has a bunch of sandwich options, some hot, cold, veggie and meat options for everyone. My Buenos Aires came out fast. It tastes fresh and fantastic. The chimichurri is extremely crisp, balanced and just the right amount of spicy. This is the type of food that doesn't happen by accident. You can tell how much care went into it. The price is a little high, but it's absolutely worth it. Grateful for the extra sauce, free water, and nice tunes in the background. Will definitely be back and will bring my friends.
Pretty good sandwiches, but didn't stand out and definitely not worth the price point. Not bad, but I wouldn't recommend it. It's also in a back alley that I didn't enjoy walking through after dark.

Tasty sandwichs with many authentic flavors. I always get the Berlin or Seoul and they are on point. The place can get very crowed with line out the door but the place moves wicked fast so don't worry. Also plan on eating your delight somewhere else because the seating in the restaurant is limited.
Great sandwiches. Place feels a bit run down.
Been here multiple times. Gotten something different everytime. So far, everything's a hit. I've started bringing coworkers too and they all love it.
Excellent sandwiches!  Big portions, so don't let the price scare you.  Good location near the convention center

Excellent food, small space, had the Havana with fried egg, $13 for same. Water dispenser is there with small cups, nice touch.  You can wash your hands while sitting on the toilet, ha ha. At least they have one. The sandwich shop is down the alleyway, look for the signs in the side of the alleyway if going north on 9th Street.
The Lima sandwich is delicious
Good local sandwich shop. Wide range of sandwiches.
Great. But you need to add Old San Juan, Puerto Rico sandwich call " Tripleta" with Mayokechup!!!  Frank
(Translated by Google) thanks  (Original) Dank

Was skeptic from what I read on reviews but once I saw the menu I knew I had to come. I walked in and I was the only one in the store. Jose helped me out and gave me his suggestions and told me what was popular. I chose the Havana over the Kingston this time and it was fire. I highly suggest it. I tried the mama Zuma chips and cream soda and it all went perfectly. I hope I get to fill in at work again tomorrow so I can come back here. I’ll be back every chance I get. Definitely a place I would franchise.

i have a few questions about the spinach soup. did you continue cooking it and add more water because it was one salty beast. Then again, the sandwiches are incredible! Ive tried the one with beef tongue and the one with cuban style. they have a bathroom and free cups of water!

I walk by this place after work all the time and always think about going in, and I am super glad I did. It's a super cool and cozy space, and the menu offers a range of great looking options. Jose and Mario (the guys behind the counter) could not have been more helpful in making a decision, and Jose walked me through the top 5 most popular options. I went with the Kingston because I'm a fan of spicy sandwiches, and it was excellent. The garlic mayo alone is a DC treasure. SO GOOD. Plus: Sprecher soda! The best damn cream soda in the universe, and they serve it. I will absolutely be going back.
Yum yum yum yum!!! Fresh delicious filling so good
Sandwich was okay. Hugely overpriced
Good, fast service.

Not worth the cost, $12 sandwitch that leaves you hungry.  I see a lot reviews where people had discounts, OK fine, but to be fair, judge the sandwich for what it would cost.  The sandwich had less meat than subway.
Very cool idea of having world's city names as the menu items. We tried Shiraz and Istanbul and they were both delicious.
I enjoyed my Kingston, a jerk chicken, pineapple slaw sandwich. The place is located in an alley it's small yet the food is tastey and the selection is vast.

I got the Buenos Aires and the cashier told me to add avocado to it, it was awesome!!! Very tasty and fresh ingredients. Thanks Josue! Friendly and Excellent costumer service! Excellent staff f. You won’t regret coming here.
Order the Seoul - delicious subs, amazing bread, all fresh ingredients, and the staff is awesome!
AMAZING FOOD!!! Customer service matches the quality of food. I recommend trying the Havana with a fried egg on it. You will not regret anything you choose here!

Their homemade bread is what makes their sandwiches so delicious. You can taste the freshness of the ingredients (like you'd make in your own kitchen) in every bite but I can't help but note that I felt like there was something missing from making it that "perfect" sandwich. I love food with distinct flavors...spices, sauces or peppers so perhaps that was missing for me. Would definitely return to try another flavor - I tried the Kingston and Lima.

SUNdeVICH is always a treat, whether it's this one or the one in Georgetown.  I feel like the Memphis is the grown-up version of the Sweet Onion Chicken Teriyaki from Subway.  The only shortcoming (and commonality between them) was the differential in temperatures of the ingredients: the chicken was warm and the other ingredients cold.
AMAZING
Awesome little sandwich shop off the beaten path. Great mix of flavors and styles.
This place has the best Sandwiches. Small but if you're in the area you have to stop.
Great sandwich place, try the Buenos Aires my favorite.
Awesome sandwiches, a bit expensive.

They serve sandwiches named after different cities. I bought the Tehran sandwich which comes with humus and some vegetables. I did not like it at all. My friend took Ishfahan and said that it was very good. The place was very crowded. We had to stand in line for a long time. Too small to seat inside and eat.
Amazing sandwiches that you can't get anywhere else. Always worth the extra walk to get food from here.
I typically hate buying sandwiches (because they are so easy to make at home), but the sandwich I got here (called the Memphis) was PHENOMENAL!!
Staff not that friendly, ambience is neat but snall inside with limited seating especially since it was busy, but food is good.
Very good food and services. Tasty sandwich overall. The only complain is they use too much plastic bags as all ingredients in each individual sandwich is prewrapped in a zipbag for fast processing.
Really good, local ingredient sandwiches!
Oh wow this place is good!
Cozy sandwich shop with large, yummy sandwiches.

Great sandwiches, quick service and consistent like the other locations. All of the sandwiches are worth a try! Prices for the sandwiches are a little bit pricey, but the quality of the sandwiches are always good.
Delicious food, but tiny place. + clean bathroom
So many options, something for everyone, meat is delicious
The portions are huge and the flavor is fantastic. Great value!
Awesome place with great food! Very chill!
(Translated by Google) Bomb off, unique 'wiches  (Original) Bomb af, unique 'wiches
The Seoul sandwich is just too good. Highly recommend. Had the Kingston too- also worth a try. But Seoul first.
A little tucked away location wise, but worth finding. A good variety of well thought out sandwich options, bread was very good and fresh, service was very quick and food was tasty.

Great sandwich, very filling. Got the Beirut, and they steak was delicious if just a bit tough. There were pickled veggies in it and they let me have some extra jalapenos too. Call ahead if you don't want to wait.
I love the food here!
Great sandwiches, reasonably quick and reliable service. Definitely one of my go to spots!
They need a create your own sandwich option
Top shelf
So many sandwiches and the 5 we tried were fantastic. It's a small space but the service is quick.

Delicious, filling sandwiches but a bit cramped at this location - even at 3pm it was packed! Would give 4.5 stars if that was an option, with the only reason that it was a little bit of a tight squeeze in the storefront.

Not your run-of-the-mill sandwich place. Great variety of sandwiches from "around the world." You will likely not get sandwiches like these elsewhere. Very flavorful. Suggest going at an off peak time unless you are taking out as there is not a lot of seating.
Amazing sandwiches! I would recommend the Kingston for something spicy or the Lima for the avocados and marinated chicken.
Fantastic place, hard to find but really good food.
Hidden gem, very good.
Its ok

I tried the Lima on my first visit. It was on a weekday, and it was too hot in the shop so I took it to go.  I understand the converted garage vibe, but the poorly swinging door with gaps, lots of natural light and poor HVAC system gave it a stuffy vibe, this made a bad first impression on me.  The Lima was good, I felt like i got a decent portion of avocado and the flavors were awesome,  but I wish I had gotten more chicken.  I think the bread to toppings ratio was a bit bread heavy for me this time.  I definitely want to try the "Rome" next time to see if it's loaded up.
Best persian sandewich in DC area
We went in late, but they didn't complain. Great steak sandwich!

This is a hidden nice and cozy sandwich shop. The sandwiches here are delicious! I had the Seoul, one of their best sellers. The bread is not hard to chew or stale. Meat is tasty. There are more options than the menu, for example breakfast sandwiches. Basically you can go there every day without eating the same food.
My favorite sandwhich place in the city, I introduce it to all my friends and there mind is blown.
I'd eat there every day if I lived next to it. Super fresh and high quality.
Small and hidden place but really good sandwiches and really friendly !
Great atmosphere and fantastic selection. World wide cuisine at a local place. Perfect. Will come again.
Price $10-$14. Very good sandwich full of flavor.
Best sandwich shop in America hands down
I wanted an egg sandwich in the worst way... and I found one! Yummy eggs, fresh ingredients, great roll. Delicious! I wish I had a SUNdeVICH back home.
Fantastic sundeviches for a real good price in a real cozy place

Great tasting unique sandwiches in an" off the beaten path" location.  If youre looking for a unique flavor in a sandwich and dont mind taking your sandwich to go I highly recommend this place. The sandwiches get 5 stars, but not much seating so overall 4 stars.
Amazing sandwiches! Authentic and fresh. Very unique and different. All the classics around tge world with a nice twist. Fast service.
Must-visit if you are a sandwich lover! Yes pricey, but flavors are amazing. Don’t miss the Seoul.
Super tasty sandwiches, we had the Capri and the Cairo sandwich, sooo delicious!!
Amazing sandwiches but they really need better AC, would highly recommend getting your food to go
Great options,  tasty
Sandwich was solid - I got the Buenos Aires. Cute shop, out of the way.
Great sandwich with plenty to choose from
So glad I found this small sandwich shop. This place is delicious and the staff is fun.
Such good sandwiches. Not a lot of room to sit but a great variety of flavors. Definitely recommend the Seoul.
This place is awesome. The Seoul was one of the best sandwiches I've ever had. Great lunch time spot.
Decent sandwiches, way overpriced
Interesting types of sandwiches. Very tasty.

Awesome sandwiches. Perfect bread - soft, chewy baguette with inside seemingly hollowed out. Got the Seoul. Was it worth $13? Ehh, could maybe have gotten more beef for that money, but I've had many disappointing sandwiches in the $7-10 range, so... I'll be going back during my week here to try more.
This is an absolute gem!!  All I can say is wow and if you love an exceptional sandwich,  this is the place.
This place was very strongly recommended to me, so I had high expectations. The sandwich I got was good, but it wasn't anything spectacular and wasn't really worth the price they charge.

HUGE sandwiches here. Consider splitting with a friend unless you're absolutely ravenous. Very delicious though, and a great value for the price you're paying. I can't wait to go back and try the variety of city-named options they've got from around the world.

The ambiance is good, food is terrible. I only tried the Istanbul, it tasted burnt. Worst of all, it outright made me sick. Quality is low. I dont know what they use as their "quality"ingredients, but they need to take a second look, including their food prep. Something was off with that sandwich. If I didn't get so sick to my stomach, I'd try again purely for the ambiance. As I'm wiring this shooting on the porcelain throne, I think not.

Fantastic off the beaten path sandwich shop.  SUNdeVICH beats out some of the other big name sandwich shops to take the crown in my opinion.  Their menu is huge but i promise you wont be disappointed.
My go-to for upscale sandwich cravings...  and the gherkins!
Good value for the price. At first they seem expensive, but the portion and flavor are more than worth it! Lots of unique options and New flavors for the non-adventurous eater. Recommend!
The sandwiches are delicious and the portions lend themselves well to sharing or saving half
Came for the sandwiches, stayed for the soups
The place isn’t there
Bread was tough

Before heading to the  convention center,  we were looking for a place to grab a quick bite.  Going off previous recommendations,  I ordered the Seoul.  The sandwich did not disappoint!  The bulgogi was marinated well and tender and went well with the kimchi, slaw, and mayo.  The only downfall is that seating is very tight and the place was very busy but staff took orders quickly and we received our orders in a very timely matter.  I will be returning to try the other sandwiches very soon!
Excellent
Wowww, A great collection of all the world best tastes with a unique menus
Great little hard to find gourmet sandwich shop
Great subs
I recommend the Seoul, Kingston, or Havana
Varisty of sandwiches that are good and filling.  Space is small and was cold on the day we went

I've always heard this place is great, but took me awhile to try it myself. Absolutely did not disappoint! I was literally taking my sister back two weeks later when she came up to visit DC.  Would HIGHLY recommend the Seoul!

The sandwiches are creative, fresh and absolutely delicious. Where else can you a good beef tongue sandwich??  Service is relatively quick, but there is typically a long line, so arrive early. The food and staff are efficient and this presents a wonderful alternative to the other local restaurants when you want to grab a bite to eat.

(Translated by Google) Sandwich shop tiny but cozy. You can choose between 10 options (they all have city names) and prepare them right away in front of you. There are three or four tables to sit on. Quite a lot and everyone we tried was very good.  (Original) Tienda de sándwiches pequeñita pero acogedora. Puedes elegir entre unas 10 opciones (todas tienen nombres de ciudades) y te los preparan al momento frente a ti. Hay tres o cuatro mesas donde sentarte. Bastante cantidad y todos los que probamos estaban muy buenos.
All the sandwiches are delicious. Personal faves are the Lima, Seoul, Buenos Aires, and Mexico City. You really can't go wrong though.
The sandwiches here were delicious. Highly recommended
Great quick bite with fresh ingredients. Plenty of sandwich options ranging from $10-$13, and the sandwiches are big! Nice murals and atmosphere around the store as well
Quick service, good food (especially black bean soup), but prices are a little steep and the bread caused some jaw pain
Good food great vibes
The Buenos Aires is the best sandwich in DC.
Very unique sandwiches. A must visit for lunch if in the area.
A truly hidden gem!
Tucked in an alley, delicious around the world sandwiches
The sandwiches are normally delicious, but they're expensive and enough food for 2-3 meals
Good for US standards. If you are coming from Toronto, don't expect much (from us restaurants).
Perfect tongue sandwich on the softest, fluffiest bread...yum!

One of my favorite places in DC. I have tried Jerk Chicken (Kingston) which is so tasty! It's a bit spicy and at the same time a touch of sweetess of Pinnappl. Also their Buenos Aires (stake strips) is one of the best! This is a hipster kind of place after all!
Cute little place with several specialty sandwiches to choose from. Plenty of sides and drinks as well.
Great large sandwiches, less than $15 for lunch hard to find in the area
Good food. Too hot.
It would be worth 10 stars, but why on earth is it not open Sunday?!

Fresh, creative, and delicious sandwiches! I ordered the 'Madrid', which was plenty of food for me, especially considering that I eat a lot on average. Good vegetarian options as well. The setting is cute and the service is very friendly.

So disappointed today:(... Absolutely used to be my favorite sandwich place in Dc.... Always got the Havana and it was always Mouthwatering!!! Today I'm not sure what I got but didn't taste anything like it used too.. What's happening?

Cool neighbourhood, deilicious food.  One of the hidden highlights of D.C. We wen't there for a quick mid-day snack and the location in an old garage hidden away in a quiet neighbourhood is just amazing. The food was great and if I make it ever back to D.C. I'll definitely visit again.

Really enjoyed the Havana, chips, and a bottled root beer for lunch on a rainy day. Definitely could have gotten two meals out of the whole thing. A little pricey maybe (about $17 total for the whole package), but I'll go back.

The sandwiches here are ridiculously good. I've had the Kingston which is pretty good, but the Seoul is phenomenal. No alcohol here, but you can stop by A&D next door for drinks (they let you bring your sandwich in too).

I got the souffle and it was frozen spinach with some egg and maybe some other flavors on boring white bread.

I appreciate what SUNdeVICH is attempting here, but their sandwiches miss the mark. Starting with the bread: the crust is too hard and the inside is too dense. I had the jerk chicken and the pesto mozzarella to try and they both lacked flavor. The jerk chicken was listed as "spicy". It wasn't spicy at all. It also lacked notes one would expect of jerk chicken (allspice, nutmeg, cinnamon, onion and citrus). The pesto was saved by the basil, but the mozzarella was on the drier side and the tomato slices lacked "tomato-ness". Since I had tried only two out of the many sandwiches that are offered, I cannot completely dislike the place, but I doubt I'll find myself here again.
Best sandwiches in DC hands down. A tad expensive, but understandable given the ingredients and worth the price. I'd go twice as often if they were open on Sundays!!!!!
Wide variety of sandwiches, most between $10 and $13. Large sandwiches which tasted good but were not warm.

This is the best sandwiches I have had in the DC Metro. Went here on a Saturday night because of the great review and a desire for soup and a sandwich and was not disappointed at all. We had the Carrot soup, Kingston, and Seoul. All were too rate and large portions. The Seoul was by far the best item but the other two still would have impressed us alone. I would recommend this place to anyone because of its diverse menu and ability to satisfy anyone's palate.  Fair warning, the portions are large and ordering a soup and sandwich both will be too much for most people.
